Class Navigation

java.lang.Object
Navigation
public class Navigation extends Object
The Navigation class handles how the graph itself is used This is done through loading the graph from a file, calculating shortest path, and getting various data from the graph.
Author:
Jayath Gunawardena created on 18/05/2023

    • calculateShortestDistances

      public Map<String,Object> calculateShortestDistances(Node source)
      CalculateShortestDistance method Implements Dijkstra's algorithm to determine the shortest distance between Nodes.
      Parameters:
      source - Node object, representing the place to start point for the shortest distance search
      Returns:
      Map of containing Strings and Object, this actually stores two Maps in it which contain details about how far away each location is and what the previous Node is.

    • getShortestPath

      target - Node representing the end of the shortest path search
